text=If I'm going to be sending time thinking about and writing in a world, it needs to be something %0athat I feel comfortable dwelling on. Given my beliefs, this means that I'm much happier working %0ain a world with a single omniscient, omnipotent, omnibeneficent god. I'm sure I've spelt at least %0aone of these wrong.%0a%0aThis doesn't mean that everything in the stories will be based on "religion" (although it's pretty %0aimportant for various reasons) or that all of the characters in the stories will believe the truth, %0abut as the author I'll always know what the underlying truth of the setting is.%0a%0aThe only issue with this is that one of the aims of this project is to write a mythology: I want characters %0aavailable who can jump mountains, drink rivers and cause cities to float on upturned mountain tops.%0a%0aHence [[the Lords of Light and Darkness]], also giving me the convenient moniker of the Lord of Lords for %0athe one god.
