diff:1218029829:1218029829:=1,14d0%0a%3c If I'm going to be sending time thinking about and writing in a world, it needs to be something %0a%3c that I feel comfortable dwelling on. Given my beliefs, this means that I'm much happier working %0a%3c in a world with a single omniscient, omnipotent, omnibeneficent god. I'm sure I've spelt at least %0a%3c one of these wrong.%0a%3c %0a%3c This doesn't mean that everything in the stories will be based on "religion" (although it's pretty %0a%3c important for various reasons) or that all of the characters in the stories will believe the truth, %0a%3c but as the author I'll always know what the underlying truth of the setting is.%0a%3c %0a%3c The only issue with this is that one of the aims of this project is to write a mythology: I want characters %0a%3c available who can jump mountains, drink rivers and cause cities to float on upturned mountain tops.%0a%3c %0a%3c Hence the [[Lords of Light and Darkness]], also giving me the convenient moniker of the Lord of Lords for %0a%3c the one god.%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
